{"TopicId":199684,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"why this strange craft \u200B\u200B\u200B\u200B\u200B\u200B\u200Bdon\u0026#039;t get into the gravity turn by itself?","CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T06:44:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T06:44:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI designed a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Spricigo/Destiny\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebasic rocket\u003C/a\u003E and it performed quite well. It even got into the gravity turn without need of steering input.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen I decided to try to explore the limits o the design a bit and among other thing I wanted to look how it behaved\u00A0\u00A0without\u00A0the basic fins. To my surprise, it don\u0027t flip but also don\u0027t get into the gravity turn by itself.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDespite being launched with more tilt than the original craft it went up. And is not that it didn\u0027t turn at all, rather it osculated slightly west-east, as if there was some sort of self-righting mechanism. Just I have no idea of what it might be.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is the craft file if anyone is interested in trying it for himself:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Spricigo/Strange\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EStrange\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand a picture\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022UuE8B7R.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.00\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/UuE8B7R.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T07:02:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo wobbling (I have Kerbal Joint Reinforcement Next), no tilting, it simply works. I\u0027m surprised that the little reaction is wheel enough for steering, with a Reliant, not a Swivel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-18T07:11:31Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2021 07:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T07:35:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223910786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221610953342\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit simply works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly what amuses me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was expecting it to become aerodynamic unstable without the fins. So it was a \u003Cem\u003Enice\u003C/em\u003E surprise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, the original craft (first link in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E) fall nicely into a auto gravity turn without steering input and this craft don\u0027t do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS:I don\u0027t have KJR but the craft have plenty of autostrust to prevent\u00A0wobbling\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-18T07:37:03Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2021 07:37  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Spricigo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T08:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223910795\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221610955330\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was expecting it to become aerodynamic unstable without the fins. So it was a \u003Cem\u003Enice\u003C/em\u003E surprise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood mass distribution, I\u0027d think \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223910795\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221610955330\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand this craft don\u0027t do it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA bit of speculation, maybe the little drag of the fins did help, moving the rotational axis closer to the center of thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-18T08:28:59Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2021 08:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T08:56:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223910801\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221610957723\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA bit of speculation, maybe the little drag of the fins did help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you almost\u00A0 got it.\u00A0Not the drag but\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Elift.\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it make sense?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T09:08:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223910809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022199684\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221610960186\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Elift\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoubt that, lift from symmetrically placed fins should cancel each other out (provided the fins have plane symmetry themselves).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-18T09:09:13Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2021 09:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daveroski","CreatedById":93896,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T09:30:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe effect is caused by wind shear.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP doesn\u0027t have wind! I hear you cry!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a completely symmetrical craft isn\u0027t pointing exactly prograde then drag caused by the wind hitting the side closest to prograde is the result.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe higher the airspeed the greater the shear, the greater the effect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fins on the first craft produced more drag on the prograde side than the retrograde side which helped to \u0027steer\u0027 it toward prograde.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery close to prograde the difference may be small. It depends on how much surface area is exposed to the shear effect.\u003Cbr\u003E\nStray too far from prograde and any craft will stall and flip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the reason some craft tumble when going into orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe upside is that if you make a craft close to the shape of a bullet without fins, it will be quite happy to keep flying toward prograde and will allow you to let it stray further from prograde than the same craft with fins would do at the same speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nD.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-18T09:32:26Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2021 09:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Daveroski\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eclarity\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T10:44:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany thanks, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022196199\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@VoidSquid\u003C/a\u003Eand\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/93896-daveroski/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002293896\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/93896-daveroski/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Daveroski\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T11:01:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlways welcome \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daveroski","CreatedById":93896,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-18T17:15:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are welcome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Hmmm appreciation.. warm and fuzzy inside... hmmm)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n;o)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nD.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}